# FilmVault

Self-hosted Next.js app for organizing film photography by roll.

## Two locations — do not confuse

| Path | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `~/Projects/film-vault/` | Application source code (this repo) |
| `~/FilmVault/` | Runtime photo library (copies, thumbnails, SQLite DB) |

## Stack

- Next.js 16 App Router, React, TypeScript, Tailwind
- Drizzle ORM + libSQL (`await getDb()`) — always async, never sync SQLite APIs
- sharp for thumbnails; import is copy-only (never delete user source folders)

## Domain model

- **Roll** is the central unit: camera, film stock, location, `shotIso` (exposure ISO)
- **Film stock** `iso` = box speed; **roll** `shotIso` = metered/pushed ISO (defaults to film ISO)
- **PhotoVariant** kinds: `original_scan`, `lightroom_edit`, `social_export`

## Before finishing changes

Run `npm run check` (typecheck, lint, format, test, build).
